children.name: Don’t reinvent the wheel with every design. Team libraries let you share styles and components across files, with everyone on your team.
children.characters: Don’t reinvent the wheel with every design. Team libraries let you share styles and components across files, with everyone on your team.

children.name: We’re published already! Edit us to be your team’s colors.
children.characters:
We’re published already!
Edit us to be your team’s colors.

children.name: Published styles are shared with everyone on the team—they can be used by all team members in any of their files. Changing these styles will update them everywhere they're used. Change these default colors to your team’s colors by selecting a color layer and clicking on in the Design panel to the right.
children.characters:
Published styles are shared with everyone on the team—they can be used by all team members in any of their files. Changing these styles will update them everywhere they're used.

Change these default colors to your team’s colors by selecting a color layer and clicking on       in the Design panel to the right.

children.name: To create new styles, select a layer and fill it with the color you want as a style. Then click on in the color styles menu.

children.name: Color and create some more styles out of us!

children.name: Just like published color styles, published text styles are shared across your team. Change text styles by selecting a text layer with the style and clicking on in the panel to the right.

children.name: Tip: The keyboard shortcut to create a component is Ctrl Alt K on Windows, or ⌘⌥K on a Mac.

children.name: Create components out of commonly used objects such as buttons and icons to reuse them across your designs. Select an element and click Create Component in the top bar or the right-click menu.

children.name: Drag and drop components onto your canvas from the Assets panel. If you’re on an Education, Professional, or Organization team, you can publish them for team members to use across their own files.

children.name: Then, click on Publish next to the current file. You’ll have a chance to review your components, styles, and to add a description for your updates.
